Looking Ahead: The B2B FinTech Market Through the Rest of 2026
The second half of 2026 is expected to bring continued consolidation in the B2B FinTech space, as larger players acquire specialized capabilities and venture-backed companies face pressure to demonstrate clear paths to profitability. Real-time payments infrastructure, particularly through the expansion of the FedNow service and RTP network, will continue to create new product possibilities and competitive pressures across the market.

Artificial intelligence regulation is also expected to evolve, with financial regulators paying closer attention to how AI models are used in credit decisioning and risk management. Companies that have built explainable, auditable AI systems will be better positioned to navigate this regulatory environment than those that have prioritized performance over transparency.

For businesses operating in or alongside the FinTech sector, staying close to these developments and maintaining relationships with the platforms and providers that are shaping the infrastructure of financial services is not just strategic, it is essential.

